source: ###Data Cleaning
#to check for missing values
print(df.duplicated().sum())

#formatting the date columns
date_cols = ['Original Hire Date','Last Hire Date','Termination Date',
             'Promotion Date','Demotion Date','Rehire Date',
             'Transfer In Date','Transfer Out Date']
df[date_cols] = df[date_cols].apply(pd.to_datetime, errors='coerce')

# Compute tenure
ref_date = pd.Timestamp.today()
if {'Last Hire Date','LOS in Days'}.issubset(df.columns):
    ref_date = max(df['Last Hire Date'] + pd.to_timedelta(df['LOS in Days'], unit='d'))

df['Tenure_days'] = np.where(
        df['Last Hire Date'].notna(),
        np.where(df['Termination Date'].notna(),
                 (df['Termination Date'] - df['Last Hire Date']).dt.days,
                 (ref_date - df['Last Hire Date']).dt.days),
        df['LOS in Days'])
df['Tenure_days'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
df['Tenure_years'] = df['Tenure_days'] / 365.0

# CHURN TARGETS
df['VoluntaryChurn']   = np.where((df['Left']==1)&(df['Fired']==0), 1, 0)
df['InvoluntaryChurn'] = np.where(df['Fired']==1, 1, 0)
df['AllChurn']         = np.where((df['Left']==1)|(df['Fired']==1), 1, 0)
df['ChurnType']        = 0
df.loc[(df['Left']==1)&(df['Fired']==0), 'ChurnType'] = 1
df.loc[df['Fired']==1, 'ChurnType'] = 2

# EVENT FLAGS + NUMERIC IMPUTATION
df['HadPromotion']   = df['Days Since Promotion'].notna().astype(int)
df['HadDemotion']    = df['Days Since Demotion'].notna().astype(int)
df['HadRehire']      = df['Days Since Rehire'].notna().astype(int)
df['HadTransferIn']  = df['Days Since Transfer In'].notna().astype(int)
df['HadTransferOut'] = df['Days Since Transfer Out'].notna().astype(int)

num_days_cols = ['Days Since Promotion','Days Since Demotion',
                 'Days Since Rehire','Days Since Transfer In','Days Since Transfer Out']
df[num_days_cols] = df[num_days_cols].fillna(0)

#  FEATURE / TARGET SPLITS  -
drop_leak = ['EE #','Current Employment Status','Original Hire Date','Last Hire Date',
             'Termination Date','Reason Code','Promotion Date','Demotion Date',
             'Rehire Date','Transfer In Date','Transfer Out Date',
             'Days Since Termination','Left','Fired']
targets = ['VoluntaryChurn','InvoluntaryChurn','AllChurn','ChurnType']

# %%
X = df.drop(columns=targets + drop_leak, errors='ignore')
y_vol, y_inv, y_all, y_multi = df['VoluntaryChurn'], df['InvoluntaryChurn'], df['AllChurn'], df['ChurnType']

# Impute missing values with the most frequent value for categorical features
for feature in X.select_dtypes(include=np.number).columns:
    X[feature] = X[feature].fillna(X[feature].median())

# Impute missing values in categorical features with the most frequent value
for feature in X.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns:
    X[feature] = X[feature].fillna(X[feature].mode()[0]) # Use mode for categorical features

X_train, X_test, y_train_multi, y_test_multi = train_test_split(
        X, y_multi, test_size=0.3, stratify=y_multi, random_state=42)

# Fill remaining NaNs in numeric “Days Since …” with 0
num_fill_cols = ['Days Since Promotion','Days Since Demotion',
                 'Days Since Rehire','Days Since Transfer In','Days Since Transfer Out']
df[num_fill_cols] = df[num_fill_cols].fillna(0)

# Impute missing values in all numerical columns with the median
num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns
for col in num_cols:
    if df[col].isnull().any():
        df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].median())

# Impute missing values in categorical columns with the most frequent value
cat_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns
for col in cat_cols:
    if df[col].isnull().any():
        df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].mode()[0]) # Use mode()[0] to get the most frequent value

X = df.drop(columns=targets + drop_leak, errors='ignore')
y_vol, y_inv, y_all, y_multi = df['VoluntaryChurn'], df['InvoluntaryChurn'], df['AllChurn'], df['ChurnType']
# Train/Test Split
X_train, X_test, y_train_multi, y_test_multi = train_test_split(
X, y_multi, test_size=0.3, stratify=y_multi, random_state=42)

y_train_vol,   y_test_vol   = y_vol.loc[X_train.index],  y_vol.loc[X_test.index]
y_train_inv,   y_test_inv   = y_inv.loc[X_train.index],  y_inv.loc[X_test.index]
y_train_all,   y_test_all   = y_all.loc[X_train.index],  y_all.loc[X_test.index]

print("Prep done → Train rows:", X_train.shape[0], "| Test rows:", X_test.shape[0])

source: # Feature Engineering

cat_cols = ['Job Title','Project']
num_cols = ['LOS in Days'] + num_days_cols
bin_cols = ['FLSA Exempt','HadPromotion','HadDemotion',
            'HadRehire','HadTransferIn','HadTransferOut']

prep_tree = ColumnTransformer(
        [('cat', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore'), cat_cols)],
        remainder='passthrough')

prep_svm = ColumnTransformer(
        [('cat', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore'), cat_cols),
         ('num', StandardScaler(), num_cols + bin_cols)],
        remainder='drop')

def evaluate(model, Xtr, Xte, ytr, yte, avg='binary'):
    model.fit(Xtr, ytr)
    pred = model.predict(Xte)
    acc  = accuracy_score(yte, pred)
    prec = precision_score(yte, pred, average=avg, zero_division=0)
    rec  = recall_score(yte, pred, average=avg, zero_division=0)
    f1   = f1_score(yte, pred, average=avg, zero_division=0)
    cm   = confusion_matrix(yte, pred)
    return acc, prec, rec, f1, cm, pred
# 1)Decision Tree

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# DECISION TREE: training on all churn tasks + metric summary
# ------------------------------------------------------------
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier

#Build pipeline: one‑hot encode categoricals, then DecisionTree
dt_pipe = Pipeline([('prep', prep_tree),
                    ('clf', DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42))])

#Binary tasks loop
for name,(ytr,yte) in {'Voluntary':(y_train_vol,y_test_vol),
                       'Involuntary':(y_train_inv,y_test_inv),
                       'All':(y_train_all,y_test_all)}.items():
    acc,pr,re,f1,cm,_ = evaluate(dt_pipe,X_train,X_test,ytr,yte)
    print(f"[DT] {name}: acc={acc:.3f}, prec={pr:.3f}, rec={re:.3f}, f1={f1:.3f}")

# helper visuals
def plot_cm(cm, labels, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(4,3))
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues',
                xticklabels=labels, yticklabels=labels)
    plt.title(title); plt.ylabel("True"); plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()

def plot_roc(pipeline, Xte, yte, title):
    # decision tree has predict_proba
    y_score = pipeline.predict_proba(Xte)[:,1]
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(yte, y_score)
    auc_val = roc_auc_score(yte, y_score)
    plt.figure(figsize=(4,3))
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"AUC = {auc_val:.2f}")
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.title(title); plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate"); plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    plt.legend(loc='lower right'); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()


def plot_roc(pipeline, Xte, yte, title):
    # decision tree has predict_proba
    y_score = pipeline.predict_proba(Xte)[:,1]
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(yte, y_score)
    auc_val = roc_auc_score(yte, y_score)
    plt.figure(figsize=(4,3))
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"AUC = {auc_val:.2f}")
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.title(title); plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate"); plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    plt.legend(loc='lower right'); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()

# -------- binary tasks: CM + ROC --------
for task,(ytr,yte,labels) in {
        'Voluntary'  :(y_train_vol,y_test_vol,['Stay','VolChurn']),
        'Involuntary':(y_train_inv,y_test_inv,['Stay','InvChurn']),
        'All'        :(y_train_all,y_test_all,['Stay','Churn'])
    }.items():
    pass
    dt_pipe.fit(X_train, ytr)
    y_pred = dt_pipe.predict(X_test)
    cm = confusion_matrix(yte, y_pred, labels=[0,1])
    plot_cm(cm, labels, f"Decision Tree – {task}")
    plot_roc(dt_pipe, X_test, yte, f"ROC – DT ({task})")

# Multiclass task
acc,pr,re,f1,cm,_ = evaluate(dt_pipe,X_train,X_test,y_train_multi,y_test_multi,avg='macro')
print(f"[DT] Multiclass: acc={acc:.3f}, prec={pr:.3f}, rec={re:.3f}, f1={f1:.3f}")

# multiclass CM
dt_pipe.fit(X_train, y_train_multi)
cm_multi = confusion_matrix(y_test_multi, dt_pipe.predict(X_test), labels=[0,1,2])
plot_cm(cm_multi, ['NoChurn','Vol','Inv'], "Decision Tree – Multiclass")

                    ('clf', RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=300,

#Train & evaluate on each *binary* churn task

                       'Involuntary':(y_train_inv,y_test_inv),
                       'All':(y_train_all,y_test_all)}.items():

            'days_since_transfer_out', 'days_since_rehire', 'job_title',
            'project_code', 'flsa_exempt', 'los_in_days']
X = df[features].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce').fillna(0)
y = df['churn']

# Train-test split with stratify to maintain class balance
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y
)

# XGBoost Classifier
xgb_model = xgb.XGBClassifier(
    objective='binary:logistic',
    eval_metric='logloss',
    use_label_encoder=False,
    random_state=42
)

y_pred_xgb = xgb_model.predict(X_test)

# Evaluation
print("Confusion Matrix:\n", confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_xgb))
print("\nClassification Report:\n", classification_report(y_test, y_pred_xgb))
print("\nAccuracy Score:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_xgb))

# Confusion matrix heatmap
conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_xgb)
plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
sns.heatmap(conf_matrix, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Greens', xticklabels=['Stayed', 'Churned'], yticklabels=['Stayed', 'Churned'])

# Load the merged data
df = pd.read_csv("merged.csv")

# Convert 'NoEvent', 'Unknown', 'Not Applicable' to 0
df.replace(["NoEvent", "Unknown", "Not Applicable"], 0, inplace=True)

#Standardize column names
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip().str.lower().str.replace(" ", "_")
print("\n🧾 Here are all your cleaned column names:\n")
print(df.columns.tolist())

# Encode categorical features
categorical_cols = ['job_title', 'project_code', 'flsa_exempt']
for col in categorical_cols:
    if col in df.columns:
        df[col] = LabelEncoder().fit_transform(df[col].astype(str))
    else:
        print(f"⚠️ Column '{col}' not found in dataset — skipping.")

# Create churn column based on 'left' and 'fired'
df['churn'] = ((df['left'] == 1) | (df['fired'] == 1)).astype(int)

# Check class distribution
print(df['churn'].value_counts())

# Select features
features = ['days_since_promotion', 'days_since_demotion', 'days_since_transfer_in',
            'days_since_transfer_out', 'days_since_rehire', 'job_title',
            'project_code', 'flsa_exempt', 'los_in_days']
X = df[features].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce').fillna(0)
y = df['churn']

# Train-test split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)

# Logistic Regression model
lr_model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)
lr_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predictions
y_pred = lr_model.predict(X_test)

# Evaluation
print("Confusion Matrix:\n", confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))
print("\nClassification Report:\n", classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
print("\nAccuracy Score:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# --- 1. Confusion Matrix Visualization ---
conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)

plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
sns.heatmap(conf_matrix, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['Stayed', 'Churned'], yticklabels=['Stayed', 'Churned'])
plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Logistic Regression')
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('Actual')
plt.show()

# --- 2. Feature Importance (Coefficients Plot) ---
coefficients = lr_model.coef_[0]
feature_names = X.columns

# Create a dataframe for better plotting
coef_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Feature': feature_names,
    'Coefficient': coefficients
}).sort_values(by='Coefficient', key=abs, ascending=False)

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.barplot(data=coef_df, x='Coefficient', y='Feature', palette='coolwarm')
plt.title('Logistic Regression Feature Importance')
plt.axvline(x=0, color='gray', linestyle='--')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
